other_tests.procedure_name: MRI of the right lower limb
other_tests.findings: Cerebriform connective tissue overgrowth on both the plantar and lateral aspects of the right foot; right foot appeared enlarged; visible discrepancy in length and size between the right and left legs; muscle atrophy evident in the thigh; hypertrophy of intermuscular and subcutaneous fat planes; inward bowing of both fibulas.

other_tests.procedure_name: Contrast-enhanced angiography and venography of the right lower limb
other_tests.findings: Enlargement in the right superficial femoral, popliteal, and posterior tibial arteries; feeders from the posterior tibial artery in the lower third of the leg; prominent vascular channels on the posterolateral aspect of the right leg and foot; abnormal vessels within the foot; dilation in the lower third of the superficial femoral and popliteal veins; prominent long saphenous vein; multiple varicosities along the thigh and leg.
